An old man with little to do
At home found himself in a stew;
He was hit with a squash
And the coming week's wash;
Though his wants were exceedingly few.

A young lady of Gramercy Park
Was afraid to walk out in the dark;
So she got her a beau
It frightened her so;
And now there is always a spark.

A young man and maiden in Trentham
Went out in a car some one lent 'em;
Their parents protested
And wished them arrested;
But I'd like to know what 's to prevent 'em!

No; Maudie don't come from the city
And her own people think she's a pity;
She has n't no dash
And her mouth is a gash;
But her new hair is really quite pretty.

There was a young man in Ann Arbor,
Who studied to be a fine barber;
He cut quite a dash,

There lived in the village of Beaulieu
A couple who'd gone there but neaulieu;
Their child was named Vaughan

The apparition of these faces 

in the crowd;

Petals on a wet, black bough.

An old man with little to do
At home found himself in a stew;
He was hit with a squash
And the coming week's wash;
Though his wants were exceedingly fewer.
